        "title": "Highlight exception throwers in IntelliJ IDEA",
        "body": "<p>I recently moved from Eclipse to IntelliJ IDEA, and there is a feature that I'm missing. In Eclipse, when you placed the caret on a checked exception, in throws declaration or catch block, it would highlight which method/constructor calls throw that exception. <\/p>\n\n<p>Is there any way to do this in IntelliJ IDEA (Community edition)?<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 7773670,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "eclipse",
            "intellij-idea"
        ],
