        "edited": false,
        "creation_date": 1318627236,
        "comment_id": 9465730
    }],
    "answers": [{
        "owner": {
            "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/0ff652685122f4500dd4f3c21fb32da2?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
            "account_id": 36734,
            "user_type": "registered",
            "user_id": 104891,
            "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/104891/crazycoder",
            "reputation": 405120,
            "display_name": "CrazyCoder"
        },
        "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
        "score": 94,
        "is_accepted": true,
        "last_activity_date": 1329885887,
        "creation_date": 1318631194,
        "body": "<p>Place the caret on the <code>catch<\/code> keyword and press <kbd>Ctrl<\/kbd>+<kbd>Shift<\/kbd>+<kbd>F7<\/kbd>.<\/p>\n\n<p>(<code>Find<\/code> | <code>Highlight Usages in File<\/code>). If you are using different keymap and the above shortcut doesn't work, use <code>Help<\/code> | <code>Find Action<\/code> to search for this action and see its keyboard shortcut:<\/p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/wU1ep.png\" alt=\"Find Action\"><\/p>\n\n<p>If you want it to work automatically, enable <code>Settings<\/code> | <code>Editor<\/code> | <code>Highlight usages of element at caret<\/code>.<\/p>\n\n<p>The same works on <code>try<\/code> and <code>throws<\/code> keywords with a choice of exceptions to highlight.<\/p>\n\n<p>Here is a screenshot from IntelliJ IDEA Tip of the Day:<\/p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/wkEtJ.png\" alt=\"exceptions highlighted\"><\/p>\n\n<p>Note that there is no way to highlight it by particular exception class until you select this class from the list of suggestions:<\/p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/IInFm.png\" alt=\"exceptions to highlight\"><\/p>\n",
        "answer_id": 7774224,
        "question_id": 7773670,
        "last_edit_date": 1329885887
    }],
